{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":714,"text":"When I was considering a career in the art world,"},{"time":4831,"text":"I took a course in London,"},{"time":8125,"text":"and one of my supervisors was this irascible Italian"},{"time":12578,"text":"called Pietro, who drank too much,"},{"time":16539,"text":"smoked too much and swore much too much."},{"time":22028,"text":"But he was a passionate teacher,"},{"time":25204,"text":"and I remember one of our earlier classes with him,"},{"time":28246,"text":"he was projecting images on the wall,"},{"time":30594,"text":"asking us to think about them,"},{"time":33487,"text":"and he put up an image of a painting."},{"time":36013,"text":"It was a landscape with figures, semi-dressed,"},{"time":39708,"text":"drinking wine. There was a nude woman"},{"time":42496,"text":"in the lower foreground, and on the hillside in the back,"},{"time":45872,"text":"there was a figure of the mythological god Bacchus,"},{"time":49886,"text":"and he said, \"What is this?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":52235,"text":"And I -- no one else did, so I put up my hand, and I said,"},{"time":55512,"text":"\"It's a Bacchanal by Titian.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":58873,"text":"He said, \"It's a what?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":61526,"text":"I thought maybe I'd pronounced it wrong."},{"time":63120,"text":"\"It's a Bacchanal by Titian.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":67195,"text":"He said, \"It's a what?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":69918,"text":"I said, \"It's a Bacchanal by Titian.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":73002,"text":"He said, \"You boneless bookworm!"},{"time":76347,"text":"It's a fucking orgy!\""},{"time":78890,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":81961,"text":"As I said, he swore too much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84313,"text":"There was an important lesson for me in that."},{"time":87845,"text":"Pietro was suspicious of formal art training,"},{"time":91673,"text":"art history training, because he feared"},{"time":95605,"text":"that it filled people up with jargon, and then they just"},{"time":99367,"text":"classified things rather than looking at them,"},{"time":104046,"text":"and he wanted to remind us that all art was once contemporary,"},{"time":108805,"text":"and he wanted us to use our eyes,"},{"time":111809,"text":"and he was especially evangelical about this message,"},{"time":115319,"text":"because he was losing his sight."},{"time":117822,"text":"He wanted us to look and ask basic questions of objects."},{"time":122181,"text":"What is it? How is it made? Why was it made?"},{"time":125727,"text":"How is it used?"},{"time":128494,"text":"And these were important lessons to me when"},{"time":130663,"text":"I subsequently became a professional art historian."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133961,"text":"My kind of eureka moment came a few years later,"},{"time":138684,"text":"when I was studying the art of the courts of Northern Europe,"},{"time":143781,"text":"and of course it was very much discussed in terms of"},{"time":147429,"text":"the paintings and the sculptures"},{"time":149813,"text":"and the architecture of the day."},{"time":153121,"text":"But as I began to read historical documents"},{"time":156958,"text":"and contemporary descriptions,"},{"time":160073,"text":"I found there was a kind of a missing component,"},{"time":163235,"text":"for everywhere I came across descriptions of tapestries."},{"time":168321,"text":"Tapestries were ubiquitous between the Middle Ages"},{"time":172217,"text":"and, really, well into the 18th century,"},{"time":175149,"text":"and it was pretty apparent why."},{"time":177643,"text":"Tapestries were portable. You could roll them up,"},{"time":180638,"text":"send them ahead of you, and in the time"},{"time":183283,"text":"it took to hang them up, you could transform a cold,"},{"time":186801,"text":"dank interior into a richly colored setting."},{"time":190923,"text":"Tapestries effectively provided a vast canvas"},{"time":195850,"text":"on which the patrons of the day could depict the heroes"},{"time":199507,"text":"with whom they wanted to be associated,"},{"time":202209,"text":"or even themselves,"},{"time":204267,"text":"and in addition to that, tapestries were hugely expensive."},{"time":209665,"text":"They required scores of highly skilled weavers"},{"time":213334,"text":"working over extended periods of time"},{"time":216170,"text":"with very expensive materials -- the wools, the silks,"},{"time":219971,"text":"even gold and silver thread."},{"time":222808,"text":"So, all in all, in an age when the visual image"},{"time":227546,"text":"of any kind was rare, tapestries were an incredibly potent"},{"time":232898,"text":"form of propaganda."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236543,"text":"Well, I became a tapestry historian."},{"time":240571,"text":"In due course, I ended up as a curator"},{"time":243575,"text":"at the Metropolitan Museum, because I saw the Met"},{"time":247131,"text":"as one of the few places where I could organize"},{"time":250843,"text":"really big exhibitions about the subject"},{"time":254398,"text":"I cared so passionately about."},{"time":257739,"text":"And in about 1997, the then-director Philippe de Montebello"},{"time":262125,"text":"gave me the go-ahead to organize an exhibition"},{"time":265468,"text":"for 2002. We normally have these very long lead-in times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271048,"text":"It wasn't straightforward. It's no longer a question"},{"time":274539,"text":"of chucking a tapestry in the back of a car."},{"time":277944,"text":"They have to be wound on huge rollers,"},{"time":281408,"text":"shipped in oversized freighters."},{"time":285370,"text":"Some of them are so big we had, to get them into the museum,"},{"time":287997,"text":"we had to take them up the great steps at the front."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292693,"text":"We thought very hard about how to present this"},{"time":297378,"text":"unknown subject to a modern audience:"},{"time":300986,"text":"the dark colors to set off the colors that remained"},{"time":303956,"text":"in objects that were often faded;"},{"time":306757,"text":"the placing of lights to bring out the silk and the gold thread;"},{"time":310976,"text":"the labeling."},{"time":312440,"text":"You know, we live in an age where we are so used"},{"time":315244,"text":"to television images and photographs,"},{"time":318256,"text":"a one-hit image. These were big, complex things,"},{"time":323303,"text":"almost like cartoons with multiple narratives."},{"time":327768,"text":"We had to draw our audience in, get them to slow down,"},{"time":330998,"text":"to explore the objects."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333923,"text":"There was a lot of skepticism. On the opening night,"},{"time":338073,"text":"I overheard one of the senior members of staff saying,"},{"time":341461,"text":"\"This is going to be a bomb.\""},{"time":344576,"text":"But in reality, in the course of the coming weeks and months,"},{"time":348846,"text":"hundreds of thousands of people came to see the show."},{"time":354433,"text":"The exhibition was designed to be an experience,"},{"time":359078,"text":"and tapestries are hard to reproduce in photographs."},{"time":362236,"text":"So I want you to use your imaginations,"},{"time":365235,"text":"thinking of these wall-high objects,"},{"time":368781,"text":"some of them 10 meters wide,"},{"time":370896,"text":"depicting lavish court scenes with courtiers and dandies"},{"time":375915,"text":"who would look quite at home in the pages of the fashion press today,"},{"time":380484,"text":"thick woods with hunters crashing through the undergrowth"},{"time":384690,"text":"in pursuit of wild boars and deer,"},{"time":387830,"text":"violent battles with scenes of fear and heroism."},{"time":393680,"text":"I remember taking my son's school class. He was eight at the time,"},{"time":397842,"text":"and all the little boys, they kind of -- you know, they were little boys,"},{"time":401679,"text":"and then the thing that caught their attention"},{"time":404500,"text":"was in one of the hunting scenes there was a dog"},{"time":407609,"text":"pooping in the foreground — (Laughter) —"},{"time":410274,"text":"kind of an in-your-face joke by the artist."},{"time":413956,"text":"And you can just imagine them."},{"time":416430,"text":"But it brought it alive to them. I think they suddenly saw"},{"time":419803,"text":"that these weren't just old faded tapestries."},{"time":422883,"text":"These were images of the world in the past,"},{"time":427374,"text":"and that it was the same for our audience."},{"time":430290,"text":"And for me as a curator, I felt proud. I felt I'd shifted the needle a little."},{"time":435847,"text":"Through this experience that could only be created"},{"time":438997,"text":"in a museum, I'd opened up the eyes of my audience --"},{"time":443080,"text":"historians, artists, press, the general public --"},{"time":447221,"text":"to the beauty of this lost medium."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451897,"text":"A few years later, I was invited to be the director"},{"time":455471,"text":"of the museum, and after I got over that --"},{"time":458586,"text":"\"Who, me? The tapestry geek? I don't wear a tie!\" --"},{"time":464097,"text":"I realized the fact: I believe passionately in that"},{"time":469477,"text":"curated museum experience."},{"time":472756,"text":"We live in an age of ubiquitous information,"},{"time":476363,"text":"and sort of \"just add water\" expertise,"},{"time":480422,"text":"but there's nothing that compares with the presentation"},{"time":484464,"text":"of significant objects in a well-told narrative,"},{"time":488348,"text":"what the curator does, the interpretation of a complex,"},{"time":493408,"text":"esoteric subject, in a way that retains the integrity"},{"time":497919,"text":"of the subject, that makes it -- unpacks it"},{"time":501002,"text":"for a general audience."},{"time":503169,"text":"And that, to me, today, is now the challenge and the fun"},{"time":506696,"text":"of my job, supporting the vision of my curators,"},{"time":511679,"text":"whether it's an exhibition of Samurai swords,"},{"time":515032,"text":"early Byzantine artifacts, Renaissance portraits,"},{"time":520116,"text":"or the show we heard mentioned earlier,"},{"time":523190,"text":"the McQueen show, with which we enjoyed"},{"time":526205,"text":"so much success last summer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529016,"text":"That was an interesting case."},{"time":531517,"text":"In the late spring, early summer of 2010, shortly after"},{"time":536691,"text":"McQueen's suicide,"},{"time":539603,"text":"our curator of costume, Andrew Bolton, came to see me,"},{"time":543859,"text":"and said, \"I've been thinking of doing a show on McQueen,"},{"time":547094,"text":"and now is the moment. We have to, we have to do it fast.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":551652,"text":"It wasn't easy. McQueen had worked throughout his career"},{"time":556389,"text":"with a small team of designers and managers"},{"time":559843,"text":"who were very protective of his legacy,"},{"time":563985,"text":"but Andrew went to London and worked with them"},{"time":565819,"text":"over the summer and won their confidence, and that of"},{"time":569549,"text":"the designers who created his amazing fashion shows,"},{"time":573644,"text":"which were works of performance art in their own right,"},{"time":578258,"text":"and we proceeded to do something at the museum,"},{"time":580757,"text":"I think, we've never done before."},{"time":582977,"text":"It wasn't just your standard installation."},{"time":585994,"text":"In fact, we ripped down the galleries to recreate"},{"time":590184,"text":"entirely different settings, a recreation of his first studio,"},{"time":595596,"text":"a hall of mirrors,"},{"time":598469,"text":"a curiosity box,"},{"time":600997,"text":"a sunken ship, a burned-out interior,"},{"time":604357,"text":"with videos and soundtracks that ranged from"},{"time":607649,"text":"operatic arias to pigs fornicating."},{"time":611382,"text":"And in this extraordinary setting, the costumes"},{"time":616343,"text":"were like actors and actresses, or living sculptures."},{"time":621777,"text":"It could have been a train wreck."},{"time":623956,"text":"It could have looked like shop windows on Fifth Avenue"},{"time":628415,"text":"at Christmas, but because of the way that Andrew"},{"time":632038,"text":"connected with the McQueen team, he was channeling"},{"time":636031,"text":"the rawness and the brilliance of McQueen,"},{"time":639455,"text":"and the show was quite transcendant,"},{"time":642262,"text":"and it became a phenomenon in its own right."},{"time":645034,"text":"By the end of the show, we had people queuing"},{"time":647548,"text":"for four or five hours to get into the show,"},{"time":651050,"text":"but no one really complained."},{"time":653677,"text":"I heard over and over again, \"Wow, that was worth it."},{"time":656755,"text":"It was a such a visceral, emotive experience.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":660834,"text":"Now, I've described two very immersive exhibitions,"},{"time":665091,"text":"but I also believe that collections, individual objects,"},{"time":670500,"text":"can also have that same power."},{"time":672705,"text":"The Met was set up not as a museum of American art,"},{"time":676589,"text":"but of an encyclopedic museum,"},{"time":679694,"text":"and today, 140 years later, that vision"},{"time":684509,"text":"is as prescient as ever,"},{"time":687647,"text":"because, of course, we live in a world of crisis,"},{"time":691270,"text":"of challenge, and we're exposed to it"},{"time":693903,"text":"through the 24/7 newsreels."},{"time":697052,"text":"It's in our galleries that we can unpack the civilizations,"},{"time":701912,"text":"the cultures, that we're seeing the current manifestation of."},{"time":706292,"text":"Whether it's Libya, Egypt, Syria,"},{"time":710621,"text":"it's in our galleries that we can explain"},{"time":713331,"text":"and give greater understanding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715403,"text":"I mean, our new Islamic galleries are a case in point,"},{"time":718888,"text":"opened 10 years, almost to the week, after 9/11."},{"time":724568,"text":"I think for most Americans, knowledge of the Islamic world"},{"time":729002,"text":"was pretty slight before 9/11, and then it was thrust upon us"},{"time":732853,"text":"in one of America's darkest hours,"},{"time":736946,"text":"and the perception was through the polarization"},{"time":739620,"text":"of that terrible event."},{"time":742274,"text":"Now, in our galleries, we show 14 centuries"},{"time":746494,"text":"of the development of different Islamic cultures"},{"time":750947,"text":"across a vast geographic spread,"},{"time":753686,"text":"and, again, hundreds of thousands of people have come"},{"time":757713,"text":"to see these galleries since they opened last October."}]},{"cues":[{"time":762888,"text":"I'm often asked, \"Is digital media replacing the museum?\""},{"time":769994,"text":"and I think those numbers are a resounding rejection"},{"time":773871,"text":"of that notion. I mean, don't get me wrong,"},{"time":777311,"text":"I'm a huge advocate of the Web."},{"time":780586,"text":"It gives us a way of reaching out to audiences"},{"time":784005,"text":"around the globe, but nothing replaces the authenticity"},{"time":789406,"text":"of the object presented with passionate scholarship."},{"time":795993,"text":"Bringing people face to face with our objects"},{"time":800596,"text":"is a way of bringing them face to face with people"},{"time":804043,"text":"across time, across space, whose lives may have been"},{"time":808609,"text":"very different to our own, but who, like us,"},{"time":813177,"text":"had hopes and dreams, frustrations and achievements"},{"time":818207,"text":"in their lives. And I think this is a process"},{"time":821386,"text":"that helps us better understand ourselves,"},{"time":825139,"text":"helps us make better decisions about where we're going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830647,"text":"The Great Hall at the Met is one of the great portals of the world,"},{"time":836049,"text":"awe-inspiring, like a medieval cathedral."},{"time":840193,"text":"From there, you can walk in any direction"},{"time":842474,"text":"to almost any culture."},{"time":845705,"text":"I frequently go out into the hall and the galleries"},{"time":848101,"text":"and I watch our visitors coming in."},{"time":851176,"text":"Some of them are comfortable. They feel at home."},{"time":855268,"text":"They know what they're looking for."},{"time":857878,"text":"Others are very uneasy. It's an intimidating place."},{"time":862334,"text":"They feel that the institution is elitist."},{"time":865488,"text":"I'm working to try and break down that sense of that elitism."},{"time":871683,"text":"I want to put people in a contemplative frame of mind,"},{"time":875631,"text":"where they're prepared to be a little bit lost, to explore,"},{"time":881788,"text":"to see the unfamiliar in the familiar,"},{"time":885610,"text":"or to try the unknown."},{"time":890079,"text":"Because for us, it's all about bringing them face to face"},{"time":894420,"text":"with great works of art,"},{"time":897345,"text":"capturing them at that moment of discomfort,"},{"time":901745,"text":"when the inclination is kind of to reach for your iPhone,"},{"time":905241,"text":"your Blackberry, but to create a zone"},{"time":910644,"text":"where their curiosity can expand."},{"time":915750,"text":"And whether it's in the expression of a Greek sculpture"},{"time":919314,"text":"that reminds you of a friend,"},{"time":921304,"text":"or a dog pooping in the corner of a tapestry,"},{"time":925584,"text":"or, to bring it back to my tutor Pietro,"},{"time":928994,"text":"those dancing figures"},{"time":931671,"text":"who are indeed knocking back the wine,"},{"time":934458,"text":"and that nude figure in the left foreground."},{"time":937948,"text":"Wow. She is a gorgeous embodiment of youthful sexuality."},{"time":946293,"text":"In that moment, our scholarship can tell you"},{"time":951915,"text":"that this is a bacchanal,"},{"time":955229,"text":"but if we're doing our job right,"},{"time":958380,"text":"and you've checked the jargon at the front door,"},{"time":962116,"text":"trust your instinct."},{"time":964984,"text":"You know it's an orgy."},{"time":968156,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":971474,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}